OL,3,CDiocese 'ashamed' after allegations
OL,4,Cagainst deceased priest 'credible'
OL,6,FThe Diocese of Canterbury says it is
OL,7,F"ashamed" after non-recent
OL,8,Fsafeguarding allegations against a
OL,9,Fdeceased choir headmaster have been
OL,10,Ffound to be "credible".
OL,12,FA number of serious allegations have
OL,13,Fbeen made against Reverend David
OL,14,FMarriott, who died in 1995.
OL,16,FChurch leaders say these relate to his
OL,17,Ftime as Headmaster at the Canterbury
OL,18,FCathedral Choir School in the 1960s,
OL,19,Fand later in his role as parish priest
OL,20,Fin the Benefice of Wye and Brook.
